Counties, waste management districts, or any combination thereof preparing the solid waste management plan shall apply for and be designated as a solid waste management area. The application shall be submitted by June 1, 1991. The application shall include but not be limited to:
A brief description of existing disposal capacity and of the capability of the proposed area to effectively manage solid waste;
Resolution of the fiscal courts of all counties in the proposed area approving the application for designation;
Resolution of those city legislative bodies in the proposed area that are currently operating solid waste management facilities or services and will participate in and provide financial assistance in plan development;
Any agreement or contract necessary to establish the proposed area; and
Resolution of the boards of any existing waste management districts located within the proposed area approving the application for designation.
